50|$|Lefcourt {{began his}} career as a newsboy and bootblack. He became a {{prominent}} figure in the New York garment industry when he assumed <b>control</b> of his <b>employer's</b> wholesale business. His forays into real-estate began in 1910 with a 12-story loft on West 25th Street. He built many more structures in the area, including the Alan E. Lefcourt building, known today as the Brill Building, heralding the beginnings of the new Garment Center.|$|R
